
More detailed README will come in a few days.

mod_mapnik_wms is a WMS module for Apache2/Mapnik. It is very basic, 
supports only GetCapabilities and GetMap, no GetFeatureInfo or 
custom styling.

dependencies

* mapnik - mapnik.org
* apache development tools
* libgd
* libproj
* berkeley-db - http://download.oracle.com/berkeley-db/db-4.8.24.tar.gz

compiling

* install dependencies
* run ./autogen.sh
* probably fix mapnik package versions in debian/*
* run debuild
* install resulting package on a server that has Apache and Mapnik
* configure your virtual host according to server-config.example

Mac osx notes -->
* export cppflags/ldflags for mapnik and dependencies:
  - e.g. export CPPFLAGS='-I/usr/local/include'
  - e.g. export LDFLAGS="-L/usr/local/lib -lmapnik -lproj -lgd"

* manually copy the mod:
  sudo cp .libs/mod_mapnik_wms.so /usr/libexec/apache2/mod_mapnik_wms.so

* add to /etc/apache2/httpd.conf:
    LoadModule mapnik_wms_module        libexec/apache2/mod_mapnik_wms.so

* apachectl configtest # should get 'SYNTAX OKAY'
